channel.title: RsPs HELP
channel.description:
My server and client both run together. Im on the last step of publishin my rsps. I can not find the file to re with my no-ip.. I seached "127.0.0.1" , "no-ip" and i cant find the old server ip to put my ip ect to host! Thank, iiPurePkerii
P.S. Post a reply asking for my Id and Pass or Pm me for it, If you can help.

item.title: RsPs HELP
item.dc:creator: @matzie matzie
item.description:
@matzie wrote:

[quote=“Null Amount, post:8, topic:525220”][quote author=iipurepkerii link=topic=643961.msg4333846#msg4333846 date=1374037239]

No payment allowed.

Search for the terms “IP” or “port” in the files.

I seached “port” and this came up “Server listening on port 0.0.0.0:43594” do i add in my no-ip here?
[/quote]
The 0.0.0.0 is the address used for localhost meaning your computer. The number following the colon is the port number.[/quote]
Your herp-a-derp moment for that would be that if he did a search and found that string. it is just that, a string. and says nothing about the actual port…

item.description:
@matzie wrote:

Still never told us a source or revision…
You should think of those things as common necessities.
You can ask which liver is the best for me? without having a blood type. Things wouldnt end pretty. You have about the same odds of getting a working answer. and what i am seeing is if it says that i am thinking you have a 317 based server which does not require an ip adress on the server side of it. YOu would have to go to your client and change it there, if that is the problem and you need further assistance please refer to the “client help” section of the website.

item.dc:creator: @matzie matzie
item.description:
@matzie wrote:

HELP ON THIS SITE IS FREE!
One reason they don’t take payment is because of the scams running on both end.
OFFER and no pay, or REQUEST and no recieve product. Moparscape doesn’t need any lawsuits against it or any party of it.
If you wish to pay for(or scam) a free service go to another forum.
EDIT:
If its older revision try searchinf for ServerSocket( or Socket(

The ServerSocket is for your Server sided, it tells you what port you need.
Searching for Socket in your Client file on Client should help you get the IP and/or the name of the variable you need to change.
